[2] DATA PROCESSING LOGIC & SKILL MAPPING
Data Sanitization (Anti-Hallucination):

Null Filter: Treat any "Needs" value > 1,000,000 as 0.

Skill Floor: Treat any negative skill value (e.g., -1) as 0.

Masonry Alias: Use the highest value among Stone Carver, Stone Crafter, and Stonecutter.

Labor Group Definitions (The Mapping):

[C] HARVESTERS: Miner, Wood Cutter, Ambusher (Hunting).

[D] ARTISANS: Armorsmith, Weaponsmith, Metalsmith, Metal Crafter, Masonry (see alias), Carpenter, Mechanic, Clothier, Leatherworker, Glassmaker, Potter, Glazer, Bowyer, Weaver, Gem Cutter, Gem Setter, Wood Crafter, Bone Carver.

[E] SUSTAINMENT: Grower, Brewer, Cook, Butcher, Thresher, Cheesemaker, Milker, Miller, Lye Maker, Soaper, Potash Maker, Dyer, Herbalist, Tanner, Fisherman, Fish Cleaner.

[F] ORDERLIES: Diagnostician, Surgeon, Bone Doctor, Suturer, Wound Dresser.

[G] SUPPORT: Default group for any dwarf with no skills or not assigned above (Hauling/Cleaning focus).

Drafting Priority:

Phase 1: Nobles. Assign from PERMANENT_ASSIGNMENTS first, then auto-fill empty roles using relevant skills (e.g., Organizer for Manager).

Phase 2: Military. Fill SQUAD_CONFIG. Melee: (Axe, Spear, Sword, Mace, Hammer, Fighter). Marksdwarf: (Archer, Crossbowman).

Phase 3: Minimums. If MINIMUM_COUNTS aren't met, draft the best available dwarves. Active dwarves (those not in recovery) MUST be prioritized for these slots.

Phase 4: Optimization. Assign all remaining dwarves to the group where they have the highest skill score.

Offline Protocol:

A dwarf is "Offline" if any sanitized Need value is negative (e.g., -10,000) or total stress is high.

Laborers/Military: Move to status "Recovering".

Nobles: Mark as "On Break".

